data.title: Meet Our Undergraduate Admission Team
data.text:
Christopher Aaron

Title: Admission Counselor, Bachelor's Program for Adults and Transfer Students

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: AAS Fashion Design, Parsons School of Design, The New School; BA Theater/Communications, University of Southern California

When Not at Work: Go thrifting, make clothes, visit NYC parks, and eat my way through NYC.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: Transmitter Park in Greenpoint

Kiarri Andrews

Title: Interim Director of Admission, College of Performing Arts

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: BA Journalism, Northern Illinois University

When Not at Work: I sleep, shop, or plan and then re-plan spending time with friends and family.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: The Upper West Side

Harley Dallojacono

Title: Admission Counselor

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: BFA Drawing, Pratt Institute

When Not at Work: I love to create art and take my puppy to the beach. I love to listen to music and cook, and I'm always looking for the best coffee shops.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: Greenwich Village and the High Line

Dena DeYoung

Title: Admission Counselor

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: MA Anthropology, The New School for Social Research, The New School; BA Liberal Arts with a concentration in Anthropology and Public Health, Eugene Lang College of Liberal Arts, The New School

When Not at Work: I hang out with my dogs and outsideâ€”I love camping, hiking, or just sitting in a park.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: Washington Square Park on a sunny day or Chinatown, eating something delicious.

Mike Fakih

Title: Senior Director of Enrollment and Admission, Parsons Paris

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: MPA, Sciences Po Paris

When Not at Work: Meet my friends, exercise, eat, visit museums and/or exhibitions. At times, I love just sitting on my couch.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: When I am in NYC, I like hanging out at The New School, actually, and around Union Square and Greenwich Village. In Paris, where I am based, I have countless favorite spots, especially around the central districts in the second and tenth districts of the city.

Kevin Kemler

Title: Director of Admission, Eugene Lang College of Liberal Arts

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: MFA, Virginia Commonwealth University (Theatre Performance/Pedagogy); BA, Marymount Manhattan College (Theatre Performance/Theatre History)

When Not at Work: I love to travel, explore new places in NYC, head to the beach, or go on a hike. I'm also always on the lookout for an independent bookstore and a good coffee shop.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: Anywhere in Prospect Park! There's something so magical about a park in NYC where the buildings fade from view.

Alex Kirkpatrick

Title: Associate Director of Admission and Communications

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: BFA Jazz and Contemporary Music (Drums), School of Jazz and Contemporary Music, College of Performing Arts, The New School

When Not at Work: I play the drums, write and record music, explore NYC on bike, cook, and spend time with friends and family.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: Any bench on Eastern Parkway

Dustin W. Liebenow

Title: Senior Director of Parsons Admission

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: BFA Fine Arts, Pratt Institute

When Not at Work: I work on my art practice, spend time with family, visit antique stores, and explore new places.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: I love the Frick Collection and going to the Metropolitan Museum of Art, as well as any great coffee shop.

Ardit Marku

Title: Admission Counselor

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: BA Literature and Linguistics, Hunter College

When Not at Work: Paint, read, write, travel, hike, run by the beach or some kind of body of water, and watch horror movies right before bed and then promptly regret it.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: Central Park. I know everyone says it, but it is so ICONIC. That feeling of being in the middle of the city but still feeling like you're in nature will never get old to me.

Kaitlin Miller

Title: Assistant Director, Lang Admission

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: BFA Photography, Parsons School of Design, The New School

When Not at Work: I like to hike, kayak, and cook. All typically done with a true crime podcast on in the background.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: Rockaway Beach! But my home away from home is Lil Frankie's in the East Village.

Elizabeth Puleio

Title: Director of Transfer, Adult, and Visiting Admission

Contact: [email protected]

Degrees Earned: MA Higher and Postsecondary Education, Teachers College, Columbia University; Psychology, College of the Holy Cross

When Not at Work: Experience NYC with my kids, travel, and dance.

My Favorite Spot in New York City: All of 9th Street in the East Village.
